🔎 Step 1: Find Your Wireless Interface Name

Run:

ip a

You will see something like:

wlp2s0
wlan0

👉 That is your wireless interface.

Example:

wlp2s0
📶 Step 2: Assign IP Address (If Creating Your Own Wireless LAN)

If all systems are connected to same Wi-Fi router, you can either:

Option A: Use Router DHCP (Easy Way)

Just connect all PCs to same Wi-Fi.
Check IP:

ip a
Option B: Assign Static IP Manually

On each system:

sudo ifconfig wlp2s0 10.10.10.1 netmask 255.255.255.0 up

(Use .1, .2, .3 for different systems)

🌐 Step 3: Test Connectivity

From PC1:

ping 10.10.10.3

If ping works ✅ LAN is ready.

📡 Step 4: Monitor Traffic on Wireless

On firewall node:

sudo tcpdump -i wlp2s0

Now ping from another PC.

You will see ICMP packets.

🔥 Step 5: Apply Firewall Rules (Same as Wired)

Everything remains SAME.

Drop all traffic:
sudo iptables -P INPUT DROP
sudo iptables -P OUTPUT DROP
sudo iptables -P FORWARD DROP
Block particular IP:
sudo iptables -I INPUT -s 10.10.10.1 -j REJECT
Block particular MAC:
sudo iptables -A INPUT -m mac --mac-source 6c:02:e0:6c:48:33 -j REJECT
Block only ping:
sudo iptables -I INPUT -p icmp -j DROP
